Here are the steps for running the retro pipeline. Let me know if you have questions about the settings in the DEF file.


mkdir /hive/users/$HOME/mrnaBlastz/
cp /hive/users/$HOME/mrnaBlastz/
cp /cluster/home/baertsch/baertsch/scripts/DEF  .

edit DEF file (any name is fine) and change organism, location of gene annotations, net files for orthology, location of repeats, etc

If genbank is not available for the genome, create  $MRNABASE/mrna.fa (sequences for all mRNAs) and 
 $MRNABASE/refseq.fa (mrna transcripts from best available gene annotation from target genome or closely related genome) 
 from other sources and the genbank step will be skipped.

nohup run /cluster/home/baertsch/baertsch/scripts/ucscRetroStep1.sh DEF

check cluster run (mrna alignment)

nohup run /cluster/home/baertsch/baertsch/scripts/ucscRetroStep2.sh DEF

nohup run /cluster/home/baertsch/baertsch/scripts/ucscRetroStep3.sh DEF
check cluster run (retros)

nohup run /cluster/home/baertsch/baertsch/scripts/filterEst.sh DEF 
    (creates estFilter.psl.gz by extracting and filters est alignments - can be run at anytime)

nohup run /cluster/home/baertsch/baertsch/scripts/ucscRetroStep4.sh DEF
check cluster run (remove overlapping retros)

nohup run /cluster/home/baertsch/baertsch/scripts/ucscRetroStep5.sh DEF (post process and mysql load)
nohup run /cluster/home/baertsch/baertsch/scripts/ucscRetroStep6.sh DEF (optiional web pages)
